history.text: hello
Hi!  I was just reading about the movie Wonder Woman.  Sounds like it got some decent reviews too!  Do you like these kinds of super hero movies?
Yes in general I do, and having a women protagonist sounds very interesting
I haven't watched too many of this type, but I like the background tying in with Diana Prince being immortal and an Amazon warrior.  Do you think you will go to see it?
I don't know. You said there were reviews what did they say?
Well, Rotten Tomatoes gives it a 92%.
that's pretty good, who are the stars in it

Gal Gadot is Diana Prince and Chris Pine is Steve Trevor - the American Pilot.  Robin WRight plays Antiope and Danny Huston is General Erich Ludendorff a general of the German Army during World War I.

I don't know any of them lol
. Is it in theaters right now

It came out in 2015, but I thought I just started seeing the commercials for it.  Did you know that the Director is Patty Jenkins who is the first female director of a live-action comic book hero movie.
Apparently, the background of the movie starts with Diana Prince talking with her mother, Queen Hippolyta.  Have you ever heard of her?
Well that's interesting Ill have to go see it just because its got a female director
I never knew that Wonder Woman was an Amazon Princess did you?
ya the only strong female leads have to be born of the gods because normal women are weak
Wow.  I've never heard of a hidden island of Themyscira.  Did you know that Zues lives there?
oh wow I did not. I wonder if she is related to thor
Apparantly Zues has a son named Ares who is jealous of mankind and destroys everything, except Zeus.
so wonder woman is gonna have to fight a god!
Well, Ares is her half brother, but he does sound pretty rotten.
sounds pretty interesting ill probably see it at some point

Oh, and also there is the Queen's sister, Antiope, who trains Wonder Woman to be fiercer than any other warrior.  She rescues Chris Pine, the American pilot who crashes off of the island of Themyscira!
after reading all that would you go watch it?
Oh yea, and there is more excitement - the Amazons kills the crew of a ship that lands on the island all the while it was really Ares who was controlling what was going on!
so Ares is the enemy

Yep.  Now don't forget there has to be a love interest - Wonder Woman and the pilot Steve.  Then Ares decides to be an earthly character, Sir Patrick, and convince Diana to destroy mankind.  But she's not buying that at all.
She also has this neat sword called the "Godkiller" sword to fight Ares with.
ooooh a loove interest
Of course, or else women probably wouldn't go see it.
right lol
There are a few other characters of World War I who are involved in experiments and laboratories and making "mustard gas" to destroy people.
Doesn't it all sound exciting?
so exciting cant wait!
Now Wonder Woman is all geared up for fighting for mankind and all that stuff!

uid1response.feedback: it sounds like an interesting backstory with a women lead and a women director a must see really.
